{"id":"madas_c4_f_q1_volume_revolution_log","agent":"codex-triage-1","source_pdf":"MadAsMaths papers/c4_f.pdf","mark_scheme":"MadAsMaths papers/c4_f_marks.pdf; MadAsMaths papers/c4_f_solutions.pdf","question":"1","verdict":"testable","topic":"volume of revolution / log integration","review_basis":"manual page-image review: q/page-2, ms/page-1, sol/page-1","question_text":"Curve y=3/sqrt(6x+1), region under curve from x=0 to x=4 rotated about x-axis; show volume is 3*pi*ln(5).","mark_scheme_working":["V=pi*int_0^4 (3/sqrt(6x+1))^2 dx","=pi*int_0^4 9/(6x+1) dx","=(3*pi/2)[ln(6x+1)]_0^4","=(3*pi/2)ln25=3*pi*ln5"],"candidate_commands":[["--int","defint(pi*(3/sqrt(6*x+1))^2,x,0,4)"],["--int","defint(9*pi/(6*x+1),x,0,4)"]],"expected_equivalent":["pi*int_0^4 9/(6x+1) dx","(3*pi/2)(ln25-ln1)","3*pi*ln5"],"unsupported_reason":"","notes":"diagram only identifies bounded region; deterministic integral is testable"}
{"id":"madas_c4_f_q2_implicit_stationary_tangent","agent":"codex-triage-1","source_pdf":"MadAsMaths papers/c4_f.pdf","mark_scheme":"MadAsMaths papers/c4_f_marks.pdf; MadAsMaths papers/c4_f_solutions.pdf","question":"2(a-d)","verdict":"testable","topic":"implicit differentiation and stationary tangent","review_basis":"manual page-image review: q/page-3, ms/page-1, sol/page-1..2","question_text":"Curve yx(2x-y)+1=0. Show dy/dx=(y^2-4xy)/(2x^2-2xy). Point P(k,2) lies on C; find k, show P stationary, state tangent.","mark_scheme_working":["expand to 2x^2y-xy^2+1=0","4xy+2x^2 dy/dx-y^2-2xy dy/dx=0","dy/dx=(y^2-4xy)/(2x^2-2xy)","with y=2: 4x^2-4x+1=(2x-1)^2=0 so k=1/2","at (1/2,2), dy/dx=0","tangent y=2"],"candidate_commands":[["--derive","x*y*(2*x-y)+1=0,x,method=implicit"],["--alg","solve(2*k*(2*k-2)+1=0,k)"],["--alg","evalat((y^2-4*x*y)/(2*x^2-2*x*y),[x=1/2,y=2])"]],"expected_equivalent":["dy/dx=(y^2-4xy)/(2x^2-2xy)","k=1/2","dy/dx at P = 0","tangent y=2"],"unsupported_reason":"","notes":"small sketch in solution is not needed for CAS test"}
{"id":"madas_c4_f_q3_partial_fraction_series","agent":"codex-triage-1","source_pdf":"MadAsMaths papers/c4_f.pdf","mark_scheme":"MadAsMaths papers/c4_f_marks.pdf; MadAsMaths papers/c4_f_solutions.pdf","question":"3(a-b)","verdict":"testable","topic":"partial fractions and small-x series","review_basis":"manual page-image review: q/page-3, ms/page-2, sol/page-2","question_text":"f(x)=(18-19x)/((1-x)(2-3x)), |x|<2/3. Express in partial fractions and show f(x) approximately 9+13x+19x^2+28x^3 for small x.","mark_scheme_working":["(18-19x)/((1-x)(2-3x)) = 1/(1-x)+16/(2-3x)","1/(1-x)=1+x+x^2+x^3+...","16/(2-3x)=8(1-3x/2)^-1=8+12x+18x^2+27x^3+...","f(x)=9+13x+19x^2+28x^3+..."],"candidate_commands":[["--alg","partfrac((18-19*x)/((1-x)*(2-3*x)))"],["--alg","series((18-19*x)/((1-x)*(2-3*x)),x,0,3)"]],"expected_equivalent":["1/(1-x)+16/(2-3x)","1+x+x^2+x^3","8+12x+18x^2+27x^3","9+13x+19x^2+28x^3"],"unsupported_reason":"","notes":"validity interval supplied in question; row records mark-scheme pathway"}
